                            <comment id="15999939" author="jira-bot" created="Sun, 7 May 2017 16:50:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1794223 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1794223&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1794223&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3780&quot; title=&quot;Heights of Characters&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-3780&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-3780&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: favor using path maxY instead of estimate for CapHeight and XHeight when missing in font&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15999940" author="jira-bot" created="Sun, 7 May 2017 16:50:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1794224 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/2.0&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1794224&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1794224&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3780&quot; title=&quot;Heights of Characters&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-3780&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-3780&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: favor using path maxY instead of estimate for CapHeight and XHeight when missing in font&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15999951" author="tilman" created="Sun, 7 May 2017 17:08:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The last commit improves getCapHeight() and getXHeight() for fonts that have the OS2 table with version 1, where there is no capHeight and xHeight. Get a snapshot here:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://repository.apache.org/content/groups/snapshots/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfbox-app/2.0.6-SNAPSHOT/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://repository.apache.org/content/groups/snapshots/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfbox-app/2.0.6-SNAPSHOT/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I haven&apos;t touched getAscent() and getDescent()... these are almost correct. The only problem is that Adobe defines ascent differently than the font itself, Adobe doesn&apos;t want the accent but the font wants them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;getHeight() is notoriously unreliable... here&apos;s the implementation for the subsetted font:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    @Override
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;float&lt;/span&gt; getHeight(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; code) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; IOException
    {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// todo: really we want the BBox, (&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; text extraction:)
&lt;/span&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; (ttf.getHorizontalHeader().getAscender() + -ttf.getHorizontalHeader().getDescender())
                / ttf.getUnitsPerEm(); &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// todo: shouldn&apos;t &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; be the yMax/yMin?
&lt;/span&gt;    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In text extraction, we know that the height is not always good, which is why we use capHeight when getHeight delivers weird results.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16000446" author="uwe m&#246;ser" created="Mon, 8 May 2017 08:48:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you. The getXHeight() and getCapHeight() methods seem to work now. But the getAscent() method works different for PDType0Font and PDType1Font. Could you please check.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="16000456" author="tilman" created="Mon, 8 May 2017 08:58:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Could you explain what you mean with &quot;different&quot; re getAscent, beyond what I mentioned in my message?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16000474" author="uwe m&#246;ser" created="Mon, 8 May 2017 09:05:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For the standard fonts (PDType1Font) the getAscent() method delivers a value like the capital letter height. For the embedded fonts (PDType0Font) it delivers a value as I would you say it&apos;s correct. You can see it in the pdf-file.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16000485" author="tilman" created="Mon, 8 May 2017 09:15:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s the opposite, see Ascent in the PDF 32000 specification:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The maximum height above the baseline reached by glyphs in this font. The height of glyphs for accented characters shall be excluded.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So the value for the type1 font are correct, and the one for the embedded type0 fonts are slightly incorrect. &quot;&#196;&quot; should not be considered. I thought about getting all heights in the code and excluding accents, but I don&apos;t how. See glyphlist.txt in the source code, there are many things that can be considered accents and I&apos;m not sure about them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The best for you would be not to trust these values and do your own calculations, similar to what is done in DrawPrintTextLocations.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17845694" author="tilman" created="Sun, 12 May 2024 11:35:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing as this was fixed long ago and forgotten.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
